<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class is used to track local variable information.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Variables that have been optimized out hold the \\c monostate alternative.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is not distinguished from the case of a constructed \\c DbgVariable</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which has not be initialized yet.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Variables can be created from allocas, in which case they&#39;re generated from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the MMI table. Such variables hold the \\c Loc::MMI alternative which can</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have multiple expressions and frame indices.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Variables can be created from the entry value of registers, in which case</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><Highlight kind="comment">/// they&#39;re generated from the MMI table. Such variables hold the \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><Highlight kind="comment">/// EntryValueLoc alternative which can either have a single expression or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><Highlight kind="comment">/// multiple &#42;fragment&#42; expressions.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Variables can be created from \\c DBG&#95;VALUE instructions. Those whose</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><Highlight kind="comment">/// location changes over time hold a \\c Loc::Multi alternative which uses \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DebugLocListIndex and (optionally) \\c DebugLocListTagOffset, while those</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="comment">/// with a single location hold a \\c Loc::Single alternative which use \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ValueLoc and (optionally) a single \\c Expr.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dbgvariable"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dbgvariable/#a5d3c7ed32eb87d635e9f17a2dd32a29b">DbgVariable</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dbgentity/#adea6ec515624a1a104a8cebee572d416">DbgEntity</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/loc/#aa1fa35229c3ab492b9ea826366f68350">Loc::Variant</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
